         <div type="translation">
            <ab>City of the Paphian goddess and of Pytheas: she, for her
part, having exalted <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">has given blessings</supplied> appropriate to a goddess
<supplied reason="lost">to</supplied> the city <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">while he</supplied> in addition to constant works,
unsparing of his wealth, has built <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/> as an offering.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For Pytheas see ALA <ref type="inscription" n="55" target="110070.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="57" target="080610.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="58" target="050303.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="250" target="150361.xml"/> and discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="V.18" target=".xml"/>.</p>
